==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[enjambement]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ɪnˈʤæmbmənt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A technique in [[poetry]] whereby a sentence is carried over to the next line without pause; an instance of this:

"The tide is full, the moon lies fair
Upon the straits; - on the French coast the light
Gleams and is gone..."

(Lines 2 - 4, "Dover Beach" by Matthew Arnold [1851])

